entry.def: If something comes unstuck, it becomes separated from the thing that it was attached to.

example.ex: The brown vinyl covering all the horizontal surfaces is coming unstuck in several places.
example.tran: 水平面上覆盖的棕色塑料布有几处地方松脱。

entry.def: To come unstuck means to fail.

example.ex: Where economics comes unstuck is when it doesn't take account of the anticipated actions of human beings...
example.tran: 经济学若无视人的预期行动的话，注定是行不通的。

example.ex: Those who come unstuck are the ones who cannot sell the properties on fast enough.
example.tran: 栽跟头的就是那些没有迅速把物业卖出去的人。
